│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                   │
│                                                                               │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                               │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                   │
│ The crash occurs in preparePlanForEpilogueVectorLoop() due to the assertion   │
│ that EPResumeVal must exist. EPResumeVal is found by scanning the scalar      │
│ preheader's PHI nodes for a canonical IV resume value. The matcher used is    │
│ too permissive, causing multiple PHIs to match, making find_singleton return  │
│ nullptr and triggering the assertion.                                         │
│                                                                               │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                       │
│ SCEV indicates a canonical IV with trip count 1051 and a separate induction.  │
│ The pass turns on epilogue vectorization. The repro shows two PHIs in the     │
│ preheader:                                                                    │
│   - %vec.epilog.resume.val = phi i32 [ 1024, %middle.block ], [ 0,            │
│ %iter.check ], [ 0, %vector.main.loop.iter.check ]                            │
│   - %bc.resume.val = phi i32 [ 0, %middle.block ], [ 0, %iter.check ], [ 0,   │
│ %vector.main.loop.iter.check ]                                                │
│ EPI.VectorTripCount is the constant i32 1024. The current predicate matches   │
│ both PHIs because it requires (a) incoming value from                         │
│ MainLoopIterationCountCheck is 0, and (b) all incoming values are either      │
│ VectorTripCount or 0. Since bc.resume.val has all incoming values 0, it       │
│ erroneously matches too. With two matches, find_singleton returns nullptr,    │
│ hence the assert fires.                                                       │
│                                                                               │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                       │
│ - The predicate in preparePlanForEpilogueVectorLoop() at lines 9784–9796 does │
│ not require that there is an actual incoming equal to EPI.VectorTripCount; it │
│ only allows that incoming values are either VectorTripCount or 0. This admits │
│ PHIs that are all zeros, like bc.resume.val, leading to ambiguity. The        │
│ earlier VPlan-level check that decides whether to create the canonical resume │
│ PHI is stricter (it checks for a PHI with operands [VectorTC, 0]). The        │
│ IR-level check needs similar strictness.                                      │
│                                                                               │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                    │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp, lines 9784–9796      │
│ (inside preparePlanForEpilogueVectorLoop)                                     │
│   Change the find_singleton predicate to additionally require that the PHI    │
│ has at least one incoming equal to EPI.VectorTripCount, not just that all are │
│ in the set {VectorTripCount, 0}. Concretely, compute a HasVectorTC flag via   │
│ any_of(P.incoming_values(), Inc == EPI.VectorTripCount) and require           │
│ HasVectorTC to be true, along with the existing checks. This disambiguates    │
│ and ensures only %vec.epilog.resume.val matches and %bc.resume.val is         │
│ rejected.                                                                     │
│                                                                               │
│   Rationale: This aligns the IR-level matching with the stricter VPlan-level  │
│ pattern (created in preparePlanForMainVectorLoop) and fixes the ambiguity     │
│ introduced by other resume PHIs that may be all zeros.                        │
│                                                                               │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                │
│ By strengthening the pattern to require the presence of EPI.VectorTripCount   │
│ among incoming values, preparePlanForEpilogueVectorLoop() will reliably find  │
│ the canonical IV resume PHI, avoiding multiple matches and the resulting      │
│ assertion. This resolves the crash for the provided reproducer and improves   │
│ robustness for similar cases with multiple preheader PHIs.                    │
